<section xml:id="section-assignment3">
  <title>Assignment 3</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Let <m>$t \in [0, \infty)</m>. For each of the following
        parametric curves in <m>\RR^2</m> (24)
        <ul>
          <li><p>
            Find <m>\gamma(0)</m>.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the direction of movement at <m>\gamma(0)</m>.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the length of the curve on <m>t \in [0,4]</m>.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the behaviour of the curves as <m>t \rightarrow
            \infty</m>. 
          </p></li>
        </ul>
        <ol>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (x(t), y(t)) = (\cos 6\pi t, \sin 6\pi
            t)</m>. (Cartesian Coordinates).
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (x(t), y(t)) = (4, \frac{1}{(t+1)^2})</m>.
            (Cartesian Coordinates). 
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (r(t), \theta(t)) = (t+1,t)</m>. (Polar
            Coordinates).
          </p></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following parametric curves in <m>\RR^3</m>
        (24)
        <ul>
          <li><p>
            Find <m>\gamma(1)</m>.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the direction of movement at <m>\gamma(1)</m>.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the intersection of the curve with the unit
            sphere.
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            Determine the intersection of the curve the the cube with
            vertices <m>(\pm 1, \pm 1, \pm 1)</m>. 
          </p></li>
        </ul>
        <ol>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (x(t), y(t), z(t)) = (t, t^2, t^3) </m>
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (x(t), y(t), z(t)) = (\sin t, \cos t, 5t) </m>
          </p></li>
          <li><p>
            <m>\gamma(t) = (x(t), y(t), z(t)) = (\sqrt{t^2+1}, t,
            t^2-2)</m>
          </p></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Parametrize the following curve by arclength for <m>t > 0</m>.
        (8)
        <me>
          \gamma(t) = (t^3, t^3 + t^2, t^3 -t^2)
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
